    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but the \"intent\" doesnt really matter if the outcome is a failed state, right? it feels like you're kind of defending the idea that even if it went bad, the intention to bring democracy makes it less of a failure. shouldn't we judge these interventions based on whether they actually deliver security, rather than just looking at what people hoped would happen?",
